# The Rooiberg Wander — environment variables (Part 11.6)
# Copy to `.env` for local dev, and set the same in your host (Vercel) dashboard for deploy.
# NEVER commit `.env` or real keys. PUBLIC_* are exposed to the browser; everything else is server-only.
# Until the PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL + PUBLIC_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY pair is set, the Rates page shows a
# "booking coming soon" state instead of the live widget (no errors).

# --- Site -------------------------------------------------------------------
PUBLIC_SITE_URL="https://www.rooibergwander.co.za"   # production origin (no trailing slash)

# --- Supabase (region: eu-west-2 / London — decided) ------------------------
PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=""           # https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=""      # anon public key (RLS-limited to the availability view)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=""     # SERVER ONLY — full access; never expose to the client

# --- Paystack (use TEST keys in dev) ----------------------------------------
PUBLIC_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=""    # pk_test_... / pk_live_...
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=""           # sk_test_... / sk_live_...  (also verifies webhooks)

# --- Email (Resend — decided) -----------------------------------------------
EMAIL_API_KEY=""                                   # Resend API key
EMAIL_FROM="The Rooiberg Wander <hanlie@rooibergwander.co.za>"  # verified sender
BOOKINGS_NOTIFY_TO="hanlie@rooibergwander.co.za"               # operator notify address

# --- Booking config ---------------------------------------------------------
# NOTE: deposit vs full is now decided AUTOMATICALLY by lead time (lib/pricing.ts): a trip booked
# 30+ days out pays a 50% deposit + 50% balance; inside 30 days pays 100% up front. BOOKING_DEPOSIT_PERCENT
# is retained for reference/rollback but is NO LONGER read by the pricing engine.
BOOKING_DEPOSIT_PERCENT="100"    # (superseded by the automatic split rule above)
HOLD_MINUTES="30"                # how long a pending booking holds its dates before expiring

# --- Operator dashboard (Part 3) --------------------------------------------
# Single admin account created manually in the Supabase dashboard (Authentication → Users).
# If ADMIN_EMAIL is set, ONLY that address may sign in to /admin (defence-in-depth). Leave blank
# to allow any Supabase Auth user (fine for a single-account install). Sign-in/verification reuse
# PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL + PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY — no extra keys needed.
ADMIN_EMAIL=""                   # e.g. hanlie@rooibergwander.co.za

# --- Cron (Vercel Cron → /api/cron/*) ---------------------------------------
# Vercel sends `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` to scheduled routes when this is set in the
# Vercel project env. The pre-trip reminder route rejects any request without it. Use a long random
# value. Schedule lives in vercel.json (0 6 * * * — daily; Hobby plan allows once-daily cron only).
CRON_SECRET=""
